ates with low intestinal wall stiffness. These findings are in keeping with a diagnosis of active inflammatory stricture, without substantial fibrosis."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020200019/asset/images/large/rg.2020200019.fig13d.jpeg" height="1726" width="2298" aria-labelledby="fig13d" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13d</span>. SWE and active inflammatory stricture in an 18-year-old male adolescent with Crohn disease and prior ileocolonic resection who presented with symptoms of diarrhea and distention. <b>(a)</b> Gray-scale US image shows mural thickening and a 5-cm region of persistent narrowing (arrows) and upstream dilatation (*) that are consistent with stricture and associated bowel obstruction. <b>(b)</b> Color Doppler US image shows severe hyperemia in the bowel walls at this level (arrow). <b>(c)</b> Contrast-enhanced US image shows severe homogeneous transmural enhancement, with quantification showing peak enhancement of 19 dB and a high AUC, which is consistent with moderate active inflammation. <b>(d)</b> SWE image shows a value of 1.5 m/sec at the area of stricture (arrow), which correlates with low intestinal wall stiffness. These findings are in keeping with a diagnosis of active inflammatory stricture, without substantial fibrosis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020200019&amp;id=fig13d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14a" class="graphic" aria-label="SWE with a mixed pattern in a 20-year-old man with Crohn disease. (a, b) Gray-scale US image (a) shows moderate wall thickening measuring 7 mm. However, color Doppler US image (b) shows no hyperemia. (c) Contrast-enhanced US image shows severe transmural hyperenhancement, with quantitative analysis showing peak enhancement of approximately 26 dB and a high AUC, which is consistent with severe active inflammation. (d) SWE image shows that the median elastographic value is high, at 2.5 m/sec at the stricture (arrow), which suggests a component of stiffness. These findings show a mixed pattern with severe active inflammation and fibrosis."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020200019/asset/images/large/rg.2020200019.fig14a.jpeg" height="1131" width="1624" aria-labelledby="fig14a" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14a</span>. SWE with a mixed pattern in a 20-year-old man with Crohn disease. <b>(a, b)</b> Gray-scale US image <b>(a)</b> shows moderate wall thickening measuring 7 mm. However, color Doppler US image <b>(b)</b> shows no hyperemia. <b>(c)</b> Contrast-enhanced US image shows severe transmural hyperenhancement, with quantitative analysis showing peak enhancement of approximately 26 dB and a high AUC, which is consistent with severe active inflammation. <b>(d)</b> SWE image shows that the median elastographic value is high, at 2.5 m/sec at the stricture (arrow), which suggests a component of stiffness. These findings show a mixed pattern with severe active inflammation and fibrosis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020200019&amp;id=fig14a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14b" class="graphic" aria-label="SWE with a mixed pattern in a 20-year-old man with Crohn disease. (a, b) Gray-scale US image (a) shows moderate wall thickening measuring 7 mm. However, color Doppler US image (b) shows no hyperemia. (c) Contrast-enhanced US image shows severe transmural hyperenhancement, with quantitative analysis showing peak enhancement of approximately 26 dB and a high AUC, which is consistent with severe active inflammation. (d) SWE image shows that the median elastographic value is high, at 2.5 m/sec at the stricture (arrow), which suggests a component of stiffness. These findings show a mixed pattern with severe active inflammation and fibrosis."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020200019/asset/images/large/rg.2020200019.fig14b.jpeg" height="1131" width="1726" aria-labelledby="fig14b" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14b</span>. SWE with a mixed pattern in a 20-year-old man with Crohn disease. <b>(a, b)</b> Gray-scale US image <b>(a)</b> shows moderate wall thickening measuring 7 mm. However, color Doppler US image <b>(b)</b> shows no hyperemia. <b>(c)</b> Contrast-enhanced US image shows severe transmural hyperenhancement, with quantitative analysis showing peak enhancement of approximately 26 dB and a high AUC, which is consistent with severe active inflammation. <b>(d)</b> SWE image shows that the median elastographic value is high, at 2.5 m/sec at the stricture (arrow), which suggests a component of stiffness. These findings show a mixed pattern with severe active inflammation and fibrosis.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.2020200019&amp;id=fig14b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14c" class="graphic" aria-label="SWE with a mixed pattern in a 20-year-old man with Crohn disease. (a, b) Gray-scale US image (a) shows moderate wall thickening measuring 7 mm. However, color Doppler US image (b) shows no hyperemia. (c) Contrast-enhanced US image shows severe transmural hyperenhancement, with quantitative analysis showing peak enhancement of approximately 26 dB and a high AUC, which is consistent with severe active inflammation. (d) SWE image shows that the median elastographic value is high, at 2.5 m/sec at the stricture (arrow), which suggests a component of stiffness. These findings show a mixed pattern with severe active inflammation and fibrosis."><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.2020200019/asset/images/large/rg.2020200019.fig14c.jpeg" height="1216" width="2303" 